# Mailx commands
mailx -a ~/file1 user@domain.com		# -a attachment and a to: sender
Subject: sending file1				# mailx prompts for a subject
~c david_haines@domain.com bwdave@domain.com	# ~c is carboncopy ~b is blindcarboncopy
Hello,

This is the body of the email 

Thank you 
~<!cat ~/signature				# at this location will run the command that its stdout will append to the email
EOT						# Ctrl+d to send

-r will send the mail from:
